javadoc: Interface for objects that can provide new instances of dataTypes

methods.name: getUniqueName
methods.comment: Get a unique name for a data type given a prefix name

methods.name: getDataTypeComponent
methods.comment: Get one data type from buffer at the current position plus offset.

params.name: offset
params.comment: the displacement from the current position.

return.comment: the data type at offset from the current position.

methods.name: getDataTypeComponents
methods.comment:
Get an array of DataTypeComponents that begin at start or before end.
   DataTypes that begin before start are not returned
   DataTypes that begin before end, but terminate after end ARE returned

return.comment: array of DataTypes that exist between start and end.

name: DataTypeProviderContext
comment: Interface for objects that can provide new instances of dataTypes
